						               													<description>A Wagering Game for 3 to 6 mostly grown-up Adults.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game consists of a number of rounds in which players draw tiles, play a dice game and then resolve the results to hopefully increase their money (called &amp;quot;shekels&amp;quot;  and represented by various coloured chips representing various denominations).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The tiles come in two colours and two levels. The beginning, or &amp;quot;Scout&amp;quot;, level orange tiles represent which game of four - Read Your Mind; More or Less; None the Same; or Knock Knock is to be played in that round. The beginner blue tiles are &amp;quot;Escapade&amp;quot; tiles, which give the player special powers. The advanced (Sage) tiles introduce more game options and new Escapades.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player begins with a set amount of shekels, a player guide which shows each game and the particular rules for that game, and a blue tile. The remaining tiles are placed in the provided pouch. On one's turn, the player draws a tile and resolves the outcome - either play the indicated game (orange tile) or if a special power blue tile is drawn, decide on whether to keep or use that tile. The game continues until there are no more tiles to be drawn from the pouch.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player with the most value in shekels is declared the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
